This appends bash headers to the file, including headers that:

* Verify that installs are completed
* Pre-processes headers so that POSITIONAL_ARGS are formatted properly

    # Pre-process options to:
    # - expand -xyz into -x -y -z
    # - expand --longopt=arg into --longopt arg
* Creates config file at $HOME/.config/<file-name>/config.yml
    * Points CONFIG_FILE to the file
    * Adds -c|--config option to script
* Pre-process Config file
    * **Add Example of Config FILE**
* Creates the ".cheat/<file-name>" file easy documentation
* Adds USAGE for Help message (Needs to be updated after running this script)
    * Add default usage for to the --help option and --version options
    * Adds options to the Help message:
        * -v|--verbose
        * -q|--quiet
        * -o|--output <file>
        * --clipboard
* Adds functions for interactivity (enabled by --interactive):
    * tst=$(interact choose "Default" "Default" "Test" "Test1" "Test2");
    * 'interact_prompt "Default" "Choose one of the following options:"'
    * interactivity provided by https://github.com/charmbracelet/gum
    * Adds --default for overriding interactivity
* Adds traps to prevent cancelling the program pre-emptively
* Adds functions for:
    * warn (removed with -q -q)
    * print  (removed with -q)
    * pass (removed with -q -q)
    * error (removed with -q -q -q)
    * info (-v)
    * debug (-v -v)
    * dim (-v -v -v)
    * print_black (removed with -q)
    * print_red (removed with -q)
    * print_green (removed with -q)
    * print_yellow (removed with -q)
    * print_blue (removed with -q)
    * print_magenta (removed with -q)
    * print_cyan (removed with -q)
    * print_white (removed with -q)
    * echo (removed with -q)


    EXAMPLES:
add-bash-header file.txt # Appends the bash headers to the file
